tasks.description:
Create src/types.ts with all core types and Zod validation schemas:
- HookConfig: { name, slug, enabled, mode (async|sync), agent: { provider, model, temperature, system_prompt }, mcp_servers: Array<McpServerConfig> }
- McpServerConfig: { name, transport (stdio|sse), command?, args?, env?, url? }
- ProviderConfig: { api_key?, base_url? }
- ServerConfig: { port, host, auth_token? }
- AppConfig: { server, providers: Record<string, ProviderConfig>, hooks: Record<string, HookConfig>, mcp_presets?: Record<string, McpPreset>, logs: { retention_days } }
- Execution: { id, hook_id, status, payload, agent_output, tools_called, duration_ms, error, created_at }
- Use Zod schemas for all types, export both schemas and inferred types

Create src/providers/base.ts:
- Interface LLMProvider: { chat(messages: Message[], options: ChatOptions): Promise<ChatResult> }
- Message type: { role: 'system'|'user'|'assistant'|'tool', content: string, tool_call_id?, tool_calls? }
- ChatOptions: { model, temperature?, tools?: ToolDefinition[], max_tokens? }
- ChatResult: { content: string, tool_calls?: ToolCall[], usage?: { input_tokens, output_tokens } }
- ToolDefinition: { name, description, input_schema: object }
- ToolCall: { id, name, arguments: object }

Create src/providers/anthropic.ts:
- Implements LLMProvider using @anthropic-ai/sdk
- Converts tools to Anthropic format
- Handles tool_use responses, maps back to ChatResult
- Add @anthropic-ai/sdk to package.json dependencies
- Write test with mocked SDK
